aircraft.

Market Sizing Mathematics

Aircraft change hands approximately every 7--10 years (average 8.5
years), creating a natural transaction-driven demand cycle. Each
ownership change represents a digitization opportunity.

  ----------------- ----------------- ----------------- -------------------------
  **Market Level**  **Geography**     **One-Time        **Annual Recurring**
                                      Opportunity**     

  TAM               National          \$255M            \$50--55M/year

  SAM               Texas             \$26.25M          \$5.2M/year

  **SOM**           **Hill Country    **\$940K**        **\$185K--\$555K/year**
                    (\~100 mi)**                        
  ----------------- ----------------- ----------------- -------------------------

Assumptions: \$1,250 average job price nationally; 24,000 annual
ownership transactions (204,000 ÷ 8.5); 25% of owners update digital
records annually at \$400 average partial-update fee. The SOM range
reflects local-only vs. extended reach including transient aircraft
visiting the region for maintenance.

**The critical insight: Provenarc Aero Solutions does not need to capture the entire
Hill Country SOM to build a viable business. At \$1,250 average revenue
per job and a target of 6--8 jobs per month, Year 1 revenue of
\$90,000--\$120,000 requires capturing fewer than 2% of the local base
annually---before counting transient aircraft brought to Dugosh Aviation
from nationwide.**

