AREA 3: Financial Projections and Cost Model

Startup Costs: Launching for Under \$12,000

Provenarc Aero Solutions can be operational with a total startup investment of
\$9,000--\$15,300, with a recommended mid-range budget of approximately
\$12,000. This is well within SBA microloan range and within reach of
personal savings for many entrepreneurs.

Three-Year Revenue Projections

Conservative Scenario: 4--6 jobs per month in Year 1, growing to 8 jobs
per month by Year 3. Total revenue: \$67,400 (Year 1), \$112,350 (Year
2), \$147,150 (Year 3).

Moderate Scenario: 5--8 jobs per month in Year 1, growing to 12 jobs per
month by Year 3. Total revenue: \$100,100 (Year 1), \$181,200 (Year 2),
\$247,200 (Year 3).

Optimistic Scenario: 6--10 jobs per month in Year 1, growing to 14+ jobs
per month by Year 3. Total revenue: \$137,900 (Year 1), \$248,000 (Year
2), \$345,300 (Year 3).

AREA 4: Go-to-Market and Partnership Strategy

The Dugosh Aviation Partnership

Dugosh Aviation is the single most important strategic relationship for
this business. Owner David holds IA certification with 40+ years of
Mooney expertise and sees every logbook that enters his shop. His
published flat-rate annual pricing ranges from \$2,380 for manual-gear
Mooneys to \$3,190 for the M20U/M20V, with non-Mooney annuals spanning
\$1,750 (Cessna 150) to \$5,980 (Piper Aerostar).

The pitch: Propose a laminated one-page flyer at the Dugosh front desk
and a line item on the annual inspection work order offering \"Digital
Record Backup by Provenarc Aero Solutions---\$500 add-on during your annual.\"
Mechanics already have the logbooks in hand. Provenarc Aero Solutions picks up books
on Day 1 of the annual, returns them within 3--5 days (well before the
typical 1--3 week annual completion). Dugosh receives a digital copy of
the scanned records at no cost---giving David\'s team a searchable
reference for the next visit, reducing their AD research time.

Economics: At an estimated 50--100+ annuals per year, if 30% of
customers opt for the add-on, that generates 15--30 digitization jobs
annually at \$500 each (\$7,500--\$15,000 in revenue) plus a \$50
referral fee per job to Dugosh (\$750--\$1,500). Dugosh\'s customers
receive added value. Dugosh\'s shop looks cutting-edge. Nobody\'s
workflow is disrupted.

Mason Amelia Brokerage Partnership

Mason Amelia Aircraft Sales, led by principal Jesse Adams (CFI/CFII/MEI,
6,000+ flight hours, 200+ transactions), operates from Boerne Stage
Airfield---a 45-minute drive from Kerrville. Their active inventory
spans Cirrus SR22s, King Air E90s, Barons, Citations, and Mooneys. They
describe themselves as the \"fastest-growing aircraft brokerage in the
country.\"

The pitch: Every listing benefits from digitized records. When Mason
Amelia takes a new listing, Provenarc Aero Solutions provides a \"Digital Closing
Package\" within 48 hours. This shareable cloud link allows prospective
buyers worldwide to review records remotely before committing to an
in-person pre-buy, accelerating the sales cycle. Pricing: wholesale at
\$1,000--\$1,050 for single-engine piston (retail \$1,500), giving Mason
Amelia a 30% margin. At even 10 transactions per year, this represents
\$10,000+ in predictable annual revenue.

Mooney International Relationship-Building Strategy

Mooney International is not producing new aircraft. The factory closed
November 12, 2019, furloughing all employees. Ownership transferred
September 1, 2020 to US Financial, LLC (CEO Jonny Pollack), retaining
the Kerrville Factory Service Center for maintenance and repair. In July
2025, Mooney announced a partnership with LASAR Aviation (Oregon) as the
exclusive provider for parts distribution and technical support for the
7,000+ active Mooney fleet.

The strategy: Approach Jonny Pollack and the LASAR Aviation team about a
factory archive preservation project. Mooney has changed hands 12 times
since moving to Kerrville in 1953. Decades of engineering drawings,
service bulletins, type certificate documentation, and manufacturing
records likely exist in the facility---potentially at risk of
deterioration or loss. Propose digitizing a defined subset as a
demonstration project at a discounted rate. The preserved archive
becomes a resource for LASAR\'s technical support operation and
positions Provenarc Aero Solutions as the recognized authority on Mooney records.
This relationship generates referrals from LASAR to the 7,000+ Mooney
owner community.

The Road Ahead: Execution Timeline and Critical Milestones

The strategic position of Provenarc Aero Solutions is defined not by
technology---scanners are commodity hardware---but by trust, expertise,
and geography. The competitive moat is the ability to walk into Dugosh
Aviation\'s shop, pick up a 40-year-old Mooney M20J logbook, know
immediately what a fuel tank reseal entry should look like, and return a
searchable digital archive that accelerates the next sale. No national
SaaS platform, no mail-in service in North Carolina or Tennessee, and no
crowdsourced scanning contractor can replicate the combination of local
presence, airframe-specific knowledge, and white-glove concierge service
that defines this business.

The financial model shows a business that breaks even on operating costs
with a single completed job per month, recovers all startup investment
within 3--5 months, and scales to six-figure net income by Year 2 under
moderate assumptions---all without external employees. The 14-tier
service menu creates multiple entry points that guide customers up a
revenue ladder while building a recurring subscription base that
compounds over three years from \$1,400 to over \$30,000 in annual
recurring revenue.

